install.sh is to be run on your client machine(s).

install_server.sh is to be run on the server.

To run, navigate to the folder containing the script and type:

./install.sh

or

./install_server.sh

depending on your needs.

Make sure you run these scripts as root or use sudo or they will not work.
The necessary rpm packages can be found in the Packages/ folder for your convenience.

This has been tested on Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6.